---
import PageLayout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { getPermalink } from '~/utils/permalinks';

const metadata = {
  title: 'About',
  description:
    'About Thyra Löwenmark—interior styling and consultation focused on calm, functional spaces with warmth and cohesion.',
};
---

<PageLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-14 md:py-20">
    <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-2 md:items-start">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold md:text-5xl">About Thyra</h1>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg opacity-90">
          Thyra’s work is rooted in practical design decisions: a layout that supports daily life, lighting that makes
          spaces feel warm, and styling that looks intentional rather than crowded.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm opacity-90">
          She focuses on calm, functional interiors with a Scandinavian sensibility—warm neutrals, balanced contrast,
          and layered textures. The goal is a home that feels cohesive and easy to maintain.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 rounded-3xl border p-6">
          <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest opacity-70">What you can expect</p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm opacity-90">
            <li><strong>Direct guidance:</strong> clear next steps and priorities.</li>
            <li><strong>Respect for constraints:</strong> budget, timeline, and what you already own.</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Design rationale:</strong> the “why” behind recommendations, so you can apply it again later.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <a
          class="mt-8 inline-block rounded-2xl bg-black px-6 py-3 font-medium text-white hover:opacity-90"
          href={getPermalink('contact')}
        >
          Work with Thyra
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border p-4">
        <img
          class="aspect-[4/5] w-full rounded-2xl object-cover"
          src={getPermalink('images/thyra/thyra-portrait.jpg', 'asset')}
          alt="Portrait of Thyra (placeholder)"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Design approach</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm opacity-90">
            Start with function and flow. Then refine palette and lighting. Finish with texture and intentional details.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm opacity-75">
            Update the copy to match Thyra’s signature style (minimal / eclectic / luxury / etc.).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border p-6">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest opacity-70">1) Function</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm opacity-90">Layout, scale, and flow—so the room works in real life.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border p-6">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest opacity-70">2) Atmosphere</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm opacity-90">Lighting layers and palette cohesion for calm and warmth.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border p-6">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest opacity-70">3) Finish</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm opacity-90">Styling, art, and texture to make it feel intentional and complete.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
